cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a new adversarial attack method against the GCN model, which is a popular deep learning model for graph embedding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the main focus of the paper. Additionally, the paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on node classification and community detection, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of transferability in the proposed method, which is a common topic in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses graph embedding algorithms, which are related to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
